        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down</placeName>
                    <date>Monday</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>My little hot-house is finished &amp; you must allow me once again to thank you sincerely for allowing Horwood to superintend its erection.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Without his aid I should never have had spirit to undertake it;—and if I had should probably have made a mess of it.— It will not only be an amusement to me, but will enable me to try many little experiments, which otherwise would have been impossible.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>With sincere thanks | My dear Sir | Yours sincerely &amp; obliged | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter and the letters to J. D. Hooker, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3953.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">30 January [1863]</ref> and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3986.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">15 February [1863]</ref>, and by reference to the payment of £4 5<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2401.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Horwood</ref>, on 16 February 1863 (see n. 2, below); in 1863, 16 February was a Monday.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Horwood was Turnbull’s gardener at The Rookery, Down, Kent. Payments to Horwood, ‘for Hot-house’, are detailed in CD’s Account book–cash accounts (Down House MS). CD spent a total of £85 11<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> 1<hi rend="italic">d.</hi> constructing and equipping the hothouse in 1863 (see also Appendix VI).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">An indication of the plants on which CD intended to experiment is given by two contemporary lists of hothouse plants in CD’s hand, reproduced in Appendix VI.</note>
        </div>        
            
